text:
The meaning of desertion beautiful .. Iftaa explain the original in it and when it is not permissible .. Video
07 Nov 2019, 11:03 by Abdullah Saleem
Abdullah Salim, Sheikh Abdullah Al-Ajmi, Secretary of Fatwa in the House of Fatwa, to the meaning of the beautiful abandonment, pointing out that the origin of the abandonment of man to his Muslim brother is prescribed for the need or necessity and is temporary, stressing that the need is the knowledge of the immigrant person in the case of abandonment in the case of abandonment He added, "Ajami" in the video broadcast live Dar al-Ifta via its official page on Facebook, in response to a question: What is the meaning of desertion beautiful? God mentioned the beautiful abandonment in the Almighty saying: "and abandon them beautiful abandonment" (10 Muzammil), pointing out that abandonment pays off when used as a means of discipline and discipline of a person who loves the person who abandoned, and there is no way other than desertion. Sheikh Abdullah Al-Ajmi warned against taking abandonment as a permanent solution to all problems and to all people because it is used when necessary and with the person affected by the abandonment. Like medicine and all according to his condition, noting that it is not permissible for a Muslim to abandon his brother above three What the Prophet said, peace be upon him as narrated by Abu Ayyub: that the Messenger of Allah ﷺ said: It is not permissible for a Muslim to forsake his brother for three nights, they meet, this presents, presents this, and peace, which begins them turning away. The fatwa hinted that describing the desertion as "beautiful" because the migrant does not break the link between him and the abandoned person altogether, to close the door completely;
